<h3 id="matrix">Matrix<a class="self-link" href="#matrix"></a></h3>

<p>As part of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_(protocol)">Matrix</a> network, we have a <a href="https://app.element.io/#/room/#whatwg:matrix.org">whatwg</a> room where some WHATWG community members hang out. Join us!</p>

<p>Note that if you go to the <a href="https://app.element.io/#/room/#whatwg:matrix.org">whatwg</a> Matrix room to ask a question, it might take a while to get a reply. It can pay off to stick around for a couple of hours or more.</p>

<h3 id="logs">Logs<a class="self-link" href="#logs"></a></h3>

<p>Logs for the <a href="https://app.element.io/#/room/#whatwg:matrix.org">whatwg</a> Matrix room can be found at <a href="https://view.matrix.org/room/!AGetWbsMpFPdSgUrbs:matrix.org/">https://view.matrix.org/room/!AGetWbsMpFPdSgUrbs:matrix.org/</a>.</p>

<h3 id="getting-started-with-matrix">Getting Started with Matrix<a class="self-link" href="#getting-started-with-matrix"></a></h3>

<p>If you’ve never used Matrix, you can get started by opening the <a href="https://matrix.to/#/#whatwg:matrix.org">whatwg Matrix room launch page</a>, which will prompt you to choose a Matrix client to connect from. Choosing the <a href="https://app.element.io/#/room/#whatwg:matrix.org">Element web app</a> will let you connect to the room right way, directly from your browser. Or you can choose from any of the available <a href="https://matrix.org/clients/">Matrix desktop clients and native mobile apps</a>.</p>

